column5: Looks like the wait dropped from 7 hours to 2hrs and 30 minutes. Interested to see what it is tomorrow.
From what I read you can hit the "Start over" button and redo anything
I think I did not look close enough at the wait times link. I was looking at the commercial flow not the traveller's flow. I assume there is a difference??
Down to 15mins now at FF
Yeah, i just saw that. Unbelievable!!
At about 5 a friend in the falls told me there was maybe 50 cars in line. Barely down the highway to the west. I think the mad rush to get their first is over
It seems that half of the world showed up at midnight so they could beat the crowd. We'll see how it goes Friday and Saturday.
Just like the senior special at Denny's. Dinner at 5 to beat the rush.
I almost would've bet that the Chocolate Moose was running a "welcome fisherman special"
I wouldn't walk in the tall grass with bare feet anytime soon........
as a reminder, you can check border crossing wait times at:https://www.cbsa-asfc.gc.ca/bwt-taf/menu-eng.html i plan on watching these after the 11th and plan our trip accordingly. phish
I wonder why Baudette and Grand Portage is not listed on the page

good question! here's another crossing times web site that also does not include those two. possibly they are just not busy enough to monitor and post updates?? phishhttps://bwt.cbp.gov/details/03380301/POV
This is coming back into US not going into Canada,just so there is no confusion.
yah - excellent point. the previous link is for going into Canada. thanks, phish
